column9: Greek, childhood playmate of the supreme god Zeus who was turned into an eagle by Hera.
Tagalog (Philippines) deity that is depicted as a bird, the first creature to inhabit the universe.

Ancient Egyptian primordial mound that arose from the primordial waters Nu. The god Atum settled upon it to create the world after his flight over the waters in the form of the Bennu bird, who is a piece of his soul.
French, dragon-like monster with wings, bird-like neck, and the ability to breathe fire.
Norse, one of the two ravens (together with Muninn) accompanying the supreme god Odin.
Norse, one of the two ravens (together with Huginn) accompanying the supreme god Odin.
Greek, one of the three named harpies, half-maiden and half-bird personification of storm winds, that would snatch and carry things away from Earth.
MƒÅori (Polynesia) monstrous bird who kills and eat humans.
Enormous bird of prey in Arabic mythology of the Middle East.
Iranian benevolent bird who possesses all knowledge.
Roman vampiric bird of ill omen.
Cherokee (Southeast USA), giant birds who scattered the Earth with pieces of serpent which turned into standing pillars of rocks.
